claim.claim-text:
11. A method of manufacturing a rotational speed detector composed of a housing in which a detector unit is contained, a center rod having a terminal wire electrically connected to a lead wire led out from the detector unit, and a resin mold covering the center rod and a portion of the housing and filling a portion of an inside space of the housing, the method comprising: 
forming the detector unit by molding together an integrated circuit chip, a sensor element and the lead wire; 
forming the center rod by molding, so that the terminal wire is held in the center rod as an insert; 
forming the housing by molding, 
electrically connecting the terminal wire to the lead wire led out from the detector unit; 
inserting the detector unit into the housing; 
mechanically connecting the center rod to the housing; 
disposing the center rod and the housing, both connected to each other, in a molding die; and 
supplying a resin material into the molding die so that the resin material fills a portion of an inside space of the housing and covers an outer periphery of the center rod and a portion of outer periphery of housing at a position where the housing is connected to the center rod, thereby the resin material forming an integral resin mold.
